"step_by_step_thinking": "The documents suggest that HCV infection is associated with chronic active hepatitis. The VA Cooperative Study Group (No. 119) found that antibodies to hepatitis C virus were positive in 27.1%, 4.8% and 3.0% of patients with alcoholic liver disease, hospitalized patients without liver disease, and nonalcoholic patients without liver disease, respectively. This suggests that HCV is a biomarker for chronic active hepatitis. Alkaline phosphatase (ALP), aspartate transaminase (AST), lactate dehydrogenase (LDH) and gamma-glutamyl transferase (GGT) are all enzymes that can be elevated in liver disease, but none of these specifically indicate HCV infection.",
